    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-07-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-07-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="714"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d714">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.24/1121½: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Madame <persName type="from">Chiang Kai-shek</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="28" xml:id="d714fn1">Madame Chiang was a member of the Chinese
                        Commission of Aeronautical Affairs.</note>
                    <hi rend="italic">to Mr. <persName>Lauchlin Currie</persName>, Administrative
                        Assistant to President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="29" xml:id="d714fn2">Received in the Department from the White House
                        about July 23.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-22">July 22,
                            1941</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Following is from Generalissimo to the President: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Dr. Lattimore yesterday presented letter of introduction<note n="29a"
                                xml:id="d714fn3">Dated June 23, <ref target="#pg_668">p.
                                668</ref>.</note> contents of which is much appreciated. Received
                            very favorable impression of Dr. Lattimore during interview. Owing to
                            rainy season and reorganization, traffic on Burma Road will not
                            appreciably increase until October, but unremitting efforts
                            continuing.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Chennault<note n="30" xml:id="d714fn4">Maj. Claire L. Chennault (U. S. A.,
                        retired), American adviser to the Chinese Air Force.</note> plans start
                    operations in Kunming by October 15th. Meanwhile hopes to enforce combat
                    training in Burma if local authorities consent. Will you please try expedite
                    bombing planes so necessary in counteroffensive. Your letter sent through Dr.
                    Lattimore received. Warm thanks for your efforts in China’s behalf.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
